defaultAdam Freemandefault: Again, since the OFT—we were quite good beforehand—if we phone a customer and the customer says, “Do not phone me at work,” we will not phone the customer at work again—period. We are not allowed to. It is treating the customer fairly. If a customer says, “Do not call me at work,” we will say, “Do you have an alternative number?” or an e-mail address or something, but we are not allowed to contact that customer at work again.
