default. I 
defaultthink 
defaultthe continuous payment authority is at the crux of many of the problems within this market
default. 
defaultLesley has already outlined the link to the issues of affordability, which has basically given many payday lenders much less of an incentive to be thorough in their affordability checks, because they have had that ability to dip into customers’ bank accounts and get paid first, almost like a preferred creditor
default. 
defaultI think that the proposal that the FCA have put forward is a very welcome one, because by limiting it to two CPA attempts over the course of the whole loan and it having to be the full amount of the loan that is requested, that rather removes the word “continuous” from “continuous payment authority
default”. It is still a payment authority but
default it is suddenly much more like a direct debit or a one-off payment, because the lender is then incentivised to make sure that they know 
defaultthat 
defaultthere will be 
defaultenough 
defaultto repay that when they take that payment
default. 
